Everyone wants to have a “happily ever after” relationship and this pressures most people to hold on to abusive relationships and maintain the pretence. People who have never been abused often wonder why a person would stay in an abusive relationship. Signs of domestic violence in victims: Victims may stay because: Staying in an abusive relationship does not mean that victims are asking to be abused. Leaving an abusive relationship gives you back the freedom and control of your own power which was stolen by the abuser.